section.section:
In order to qualify for an exemption under paragraph (1) of this subsection, all owners of the motor vehicle shall certify the following:
That the owner of the motor vehicle meets the disability requirements of § 13-616(b)(1) of this article;
That the motor vehicle has been issued a special disabled person's registration number and special registration plates under § 13-616 of this article;
That the motor vehicle is driven 5,000 miles or less annually; and
The motor vehicle's odometer reading at the time of the certification.
